WordPress modification hierarchy

When implementing changes in this project, follow the WordPress override hierarchy and never modify upstream code unless explicitly instructed.

Priority order for modifications:

1. Child theme  
   wp-content/themes/vantagepictures-child  
   This is the primary location for all custom code, styling, templates, and overrides.

2. Custom plugins  
   wp-content/plugins/vp-*  
   Use only when functionality should not belong to the theme.

3. Parent theme (reference only)  
   wp-content/themes/vantagepictures  
   Inspect for structure and behavior, but do not modify unless explicitly instructed.

4. Third-party plugins (reference only)  
   wp-content/plugins/*  
   Never modify plugin source code unless explicitly instructed.

5. WordPress core (never modify)  
   wp-admin  
   wp-includes  

If a change appears to require editing plugin or core files, implement the change using:
- child theme overrides
- hooks or filters
- custom CSS/JS
- wrapper functions
- custom plugins

Direct modification of WordPress core or third-party plugins is prohibited.
